and \"that sounds like [[Mac DeMarco|Mac [DeMarco]]]\". The pair's early recordings were made by holding instruments to the internal microphone of an [[iPad]] running [[GarageBand]].<ref name=\"JonesOberlin2018\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.oberlin.edu/news/qa-vansire-cofounder-josh-augustin-20|title=Q&A with Vansire Cofounder Josh Augustin \u201920|last=Jones|first=Ben|date=7 December 2018|website=Oberlin College and Conservatory|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200224080520/https://www.oberlin.edu/news/qa-vansire-cofounder-josh-augustin-20|archive-date=24 February 2020|access-date=27 March 2020}}</ref> Augustin and Winemiller, initially unsure of what to call their new project, turned to an online random word generator which landed on \"vansire\",<ref name=\"JonesOberlin2018\" /> an alternative name for the [[Marsh mongoose]].<ref name=\"KingdonHappold2013\">{{cite book|author1=Jonathan Kingdon|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=B_07noCPc4kC&pg=RA4-PA298|title=Mammals of Africa|author2=David Happold|author3=Thomas Butynski|date=23 May 2013|publisher=A&amp;C Black|others=Michael Hoffmann, Meredith Happold, Jan Kalina|isbn=978-1-4081-8996-2|pages=298}}</ref>\n\nFrom there, the two continued to record together in their basements, living rooms, and bedrooms under the new Vansire moniker.\n\n=== ''Reflections and Reveries'' and ''The Rolling, Driftless North'' (2016-2017) ===\nIn August 2016, Vansire self-released their first album, ''Reflections and Reveries''. The duo recorded the album entirely in Winemiller's basement in a roughly one-year period from August 2015 to August 2016, and included Winemiller's brother, Issac, on bass for some songs.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://vansire.bandcamp.com/album/reflections-and-reveries|title=Reflections and Reveries - Vansire|last=|first=|date=|website=Bandcamp|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=28 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.complex.com/pigeons-and-planes/2018/