. The school administration was mandated to develop a school Improvement Plan to address the low student achievement. West Hazleton Elementary/Middle School was in '''School Improvement I''' due to chronic low performance of its students.<ref>Pennsylvania Department of Education, West Hazleton Elementary/Middle School AYP Overview, September 14, 2009</ref>\n\n;'''8th Grade Reading:'''\n*2012 - 68% on grade level (16% below basic). In Pennsylvania, 79% of 8th graders on grade level.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://paayp.emetric.net/Content/reportcards/RC11S118403302000007569.PDF |title=West Hazleton Elementary/Middle School Academic Achievement Report Card 2012 |author=Pennsylvania Department of Education |date=September 21, 2012 }}{{dead link|date=April 2018 |bot=Ost316 |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>\n*2011 - 63%  (21% below basic). State - 81.8%<ref>{{cite web |url=http://paayp.emetric.net/Content/reportcards/RC11S118403302000007569.PDF |title=West Hazleton Elementary/Middle School Academic Achievement Report Card 2011 |author=Pennsylvania Department of Education |date=September 29, 2011 }}{{dead link|date=April 2018 |bot=Ost316 |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>\n*2010 - 68% (19% below basic). State - 81%\n*2009 - 69%. State: 80.9%<ref>Pennsylvania Department of Education, West Hazleton Elementary/Middle School Academic Achievement Report Card 2009, September 14, 2009</ref>\n*2008 - 66%, State - 78%<ref>Pennsylvania Department of Education, West Hazleton Elementary/Middle School Academic Achievement Report Card 2008, August 15, 2008</ref>\n\nIn 2009, 57% of males (2008\u201369%) and 77% (2008 - 64%) of females are on grade level for reading in eighth grade.\n\n;'''8th Grade Math:'''\n*2012 - 67% on grade level (15% below basic). State - 76%\n*2011 - 65% on grade level (20% below basic). State - 76.9%\n*2010 - 60% (18% below basic). State - 75%\n*2009 - 73%, State - 71%\n*2008 - 50%, State - 70%\n\n;'''8th Grade Science:'''\n*2012 - 34% on grade level (33% below basic). State \u2