ool is located at 400 Alvin Street, Freeland. In 2010, the school enrolled 895 pupils ( kindergarten through 8th grade). The school employed 55 teachers, yielding a student\u2013teacher ratio of 16:1. Seventy-eight students were Hispanic, 784 were Caucasian and 21 were black.<ref>National Center for Education Statistics, Common Care of Data - Freeland Elementary/Middle School, 2010</ref> In 2011 and 2010, the school achieved '''AYP''' status.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://paayp.emetric.net/School/Overview/c40/118403302/6718 |title=Freeland Elementary Middle School AYP Overview |author=Pennsylvania Department of Education |date=September 29, 2011 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121005231252/http://paayp.emetric.net/School/Overview/c40/118403302/6718 |archivedate=October 5, 2012 }}</ref>\n\n'''PSSA Results: '''\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-1-of-2}}\n'''8th Grade Reading'''\n*2011 - 71% on grade level (20% below basic). State - 81.8%<ref>{{cite web |url=http://paayp.emetric.net/Content/reportcards/RC11S118403302000006718.PDF |title=Freeland Elementary Middle School Academic Achievement Report Card 2011 |author=Pennsylvania Department of Education |date=September 29, 2011 }}{{dead link|date=April 2018 |bot=Ost316 |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>\n*2010 - 83% (11% below basic). State - 81%<ref>Pennsylvania Department of Education, Freeland Elementary Middle School Academic Achievement Report Card 2011, September 29, 2011</ref>\n{{col-2-of-2}}\n'''8th Grade Math:'''\n*2011 - 55% on grade level (24% below basic). State - 76.9%\n*2010 - 64% (18% below basic). State - 75%\n{{col-end}}\n\n'''8th Grade Science:'''\n*2011 - 44% on grade level (32% below basic). State \u2013 58.3%\n*2010 - 39%, (33% below basic). State \u2013 57%\n\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-1-of-2}}\n'''7th Grade Reading'''\n*2011 - 72% on grade level (13% below basic). State \u2013 76%\n*2010 - 66% (21% below basic). State - 73%\n{{col-2-of-2}}\n'''7th Grade Math:'''\n*2011 - 75% on grade level (12% bel