       = \u2192 [[Ypiranga Futebol Clube|Ypiranga-RS]] (loan)\n| clubs24             = [[Treze Futebol Clube|Treze]]\n| clubs25             = [[Associa\u00e7\u00e3o Portuguesa de Desportos|Portuguesa]]\n| clubs26             = [[Treze Futebol Clube|Treze]]\n| clubs27             = [[Associa\u00e7\u00e3o Desportiva Perilima|Perilima]]\n| clubs28             = [[Treze Futebol Clube|Treze]]\n| clubs29             = [[Associa\u00e7\u00e3o Desportiva Perilima|Perilima]]\n| caps1               = 0 \n| goals1              = 0\n| caps2               = 0\n| goals2              = 0\n| caps3               = 7\n| goals3              = 0\n| caps4               = 42\n| goals4              = 7\n| caps5               = 60\n| goals5              = 15\n| caps6               = 19\n| goals6              = 3\n| caps7               = 49\n| goals7              = 23\n| caps8               = 155\n| goals8              = 65\n| caps9               = 17\n| goals9              = 2\n| caps10              = 51\n| goals10             = 12\n| caps11              = 7\n| goals11             = 8\n| caps12              = 34\n| goals12             = 14\n| caps13              = 8\n| goals13             = 1\n| caps14              = 23\n| goals14             = 6\n| caps15              = 33\n| goals15             = 12\n| caps16              = 19\n| goals16             = 3\n| caps17              = 33\n| goals17             = 5\n| caps18              = 19\n| goals18             = 2\n| caps19              = 17\n| goals19             = 9\n| caps20              = 32\n| goals20             = 5\n| caps21              = 14\n| goals21             = 4\n| caps22              = 9\n| goals22             = 3\n| caps23              = 4\n| goals23             = 2\n| caps24              = 4\n| goals24             = 4\n| caps25              = 6\n| goals25             = 0\n| caps26              = 13\n| goals26             = 5\n| caps27              = 2\n| goals27             = 2\n| caps28              = 16\n| goals28             = 3\n| caps29             = 3\n| goals29             = 0\n| nationalyears1      = 2001\n| nationalteam1       = [[Brazil national football team|Brazil]]\n| nationalcaps1       = 5\n| nationalgoals1      = 1\n| medaltemplates      = \n| club-update         = 24 August 2019<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ogol.com.br/player.php?id=4620|title=Perfil de Marcelinho Para\u00edba|publisher=O Gol|accessdate= 19 September 2016 |date= 19 September 2016|language=Portuguese}}</ref>\n| nationalteam-update = \n}}\n\n'''Marcelo dos Santos''' (born 17 May 1975), known as '''Marcelinho Para\u00edba''' or simply '''Marcelinho''', is a former Brazilian [[Association football|footballer]] who last played for [[Associa\u00e7\u00e3o Desportiva Perilima|AD Perilima]] as an [[Midfielder#Attacking midfielder|attacking midfielder]].\n\nIn [[Brazil]], he is also known as '''Marcelinho ''Para\u00edba''''', which refers to the state in which he was born, as a means to distinguish himself from [[Marcelinho|other players also called \"Marcelinho\"]]. He was arguably one of the best [[playmakers]] in the [[Bundesliga]] because of his extravagant skills that include his visionary passing, abundance of tricks, and his world class technique.\n\n==Career==\nBorn in [[Campina Grande]], [[Para\u00edba]], Marcelinho Paraiba began his career in [[Campinense Clube|Campinense]], where he won two league titles there. Between 1994 and 1995, he played for [[Santos FC|Santos]]. Two years later, however, he made his breakthrough at [[S\u00e3o Paulo FC|S\u00e3o Paulo]], where he won two Paulist\u00f5es before being sold to [[Olympique de Marseille|Marseille]].\n\nHe only spent a year in France, and in 2001 he returned to Brazil to play for [[Gr\u00eamio Foot-Ball Porto Alegrense|Gr\u00eamio]], where he began to experience the pinnacle of his career. At that time, Marcelinho Paraiba was called \"Marcelinho Para\u00facho\" by Gremistas, because of his passage in the team. He became champion and top scorer of the Campeonato Ga\u00facho, and champion of the [[Copa do Brasil]], where he scored a goal in the second game in the final against Corinthians, but did not play in the league that year because before the tournament, he signed a five-year contract with [[Hertha BSC]].\n\nMarcelinho played for Hertha from 2001 to 2006. He is ranked among the most important players in the association's history and there Marcelinho was known as a technically talented player, serving as a [[playmaker]] and leader while performing in both the midfield and forward area. In addition, he carried the responsibility of executing the [[Direct free kick|free kicks]], [[corner kick]]s, and [[Penalty kick (association football)|penalty kick]]s of the club. The personal trademarks of this extravagant football player are his usually remarkable shoes and his often multicoloured hair. He was capped fives times for the [[Brazil national football team]], for which he scored once. At the beginning of the 2006\u201307 season, he arbitrarily extended his off-season vacation by nine days, which led to some slight tension with the Hertha association management. After Marcelinho had expressed himself, in the following the days, contradictory statements as to whether he wanted to remain at Hertha or not, he ended his term with them, signing a three-year contract with [[Turkey|Turkish]] club [[Trabzonspor]] for approximately 2.5 million [[euro]]s.\n\nIn August 2008, Marcelinho Para\u00edba returned to Brazil to play for [[Clube de Regatas do Flamengo|Flamengo]].<ref name=\"flamengo\">{{cite web|url=http://esportes.terra.com.br/futebol/brasileiro/2008/interna/0,,OI3074725-EI11421,00-Flamengo+acerta+com+meia+Marcelinho+Paraiba.html|title=Flamengo acerta com meia Marcelinho Para\u00edba|publisher=Terra Esportes|accessdate= 10 August 2008 |date= 10 August 2008|language=Portuguese}}</ref> On 6 March 2009, [[Coritiba Foot Ball Club|Coritiba]] signed the forward on a free transfer until the end of the year, as Marcelinho terminated his contract with Flamengo.<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.coritiba.com.br/site/index.php?pag=noticias&n_cod=7263&n_titulo=Coxa-e-Marcelinho-perto-de-acerto | title = Coxa e Marcelinho perto de acerto | language = Portuguese | date = 6 March 2009 | accessdate = 2 October 2010 | publisher = coritiba.com.br | url-status = dead | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20090310011633/http://www.coritiba.com.br/site/index.php?pag=noticias&n_cod=7263&n_titulo=Coxa-e-Marcelinho-perto-de-acerto | archivedate = 10 March 2009 | df = dmy-all }}</ref> After the relegation of Coritiba, he re-signed for S\u00e3o Paulo on 18 December 2009. On 9 August 2010 he was loaned to [[Sport Club do Recife|Sport]] till the end of the 2010 season<ref>{{cite web | url = http://esporte.uol.com.br/futebol/ultimas-noticias/2010/08/09/marcelinho-paraiba-deixa-o-sao-paulo-e-acerta-para-reforcar-o-sport.jhtm | title = Marcelinho Para\u00edba deixa o S\u00e3o Paulo e acerta para refor\u00e7ar o Sport | date = 9 August 2010 | accessdate = 2 October 2010 | publisher = Esporte | language = Portuguese}}</ref> and his contract was extended to the end of the 2011 season.\n\nMarcelinho subsequently represented Sport, [[Boa Esporte Clube|Boa Esporte]], [[Fortaleza Esporte Clube|Fortaleza]], [[Esporte Clube Internacional (SC)|Internacional de Lages]] (two stints), [[Joinville Esporte Clube|Joinville]], [[Oeste Futebol Clube|Oeste]], [[Ypiranga Futebol Clube|Ypiranga de Erechim]] [[Treze Futebol Clube|Treze]]<ref>{{cite web | url = http://globoesporte.globo.com/pb/futebol/times/treze/noticia/2016/11/meia-marcelinho-paraiba-da-drible-no-campinense-e-fecha-com-o-rival-treze.html | title = Meia Marcelinho Para\u00edba d\u00e1 drible no Campinense e fecha com o rival Treze | website = globoesporte.globo.com | date = 29 November 2016 | access-date = 29 November 2016}}</ref> and [[Associa\u00e7\u00e3o Portuguesa de Desportos|Portuguesa]].\n\n===Retire===\nOn 15 March 2020, he made his last game as a professional player, playing for [[Associa\u00e7\u00e3o Desportiva Perilima|Perilima]] against [[Centro Sportivo Paraibano]] for the eighth round of the [[2020 Campeonato Paraibano]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Marcelinho Para\u00edba encerra carreira pol\u00eamica no jogo de hoje contra o CSP \u2022 Para\u00edba Online |url=https://paraibaonline.com.br/esportes/marcelinho-paraiba-encerra-carreira-polemica-no-jogo-de-hoje-contra-o-csp/ |website=Para\u00edba Online |date=15 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Honours==\n===Club===\n'''Campinense'''<ref name=\"hons\">{{cite web|title=Biografias \u2013 Marcelinho Para\u00edba|url=http://esporte.uol.com.br/futebol/biografias/139/marcelinho-paraiba/|publisher=Uol Esporte|accessdate=20 March 2015|language=Portuguese}}</ref>\n*[[Campeonato Paraibano]]: 1991, 1993\n\n'''S\u00e3o Paulo'''<ref name=\"hons\" />\n*[[Campeonato Paulista]]: 1998, 2000\n\n'''Gr\u00eamio'''<ref name=\"hons\" />\n*[[Campeonato Ga\u00facho]]: 2001\n*[[Copa do Brasil]]: [[Copa do Brasil 2001|2001]]\n\n'''Hertha BSC'''\n*[[DFB-Ligapokal]]: 2001, 2002\n\n'''Boa Esporte'''\n*[[Ta\u00e7a Minas Gerais]]: 2012<ref>{{cite web|title=Boa Esporte segura o Le\u00e3o e \u00e9 campe\u00e3o da Ta\u00e7a Minas Gerais 2012|url=http://www.hojeemdia.com.br/esportes/boa-esporte-segura-o-le-o-e-e-campe-o-da-taca-minas-gerais-2012-1.66229|publisher=www.hojeemdia.com|accessdate=20 March 2015|language=Portuguese|date=9 December 2012}}</ref>\n\n===Individual===\n*''[[Kicker (sports magazine)|kicker]]'' [[Bundesliga]] Team of the Season: 2002\u201303, 2004\u201305<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.kicker.de/news/fussball/bundesliga/bl50/200203/startseite.html|title=Bundesliga Historie 2002/03|language=German|publisher=kicker}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.kicker.de/news/fussball/bundesliga/bl50/200405/startseite.html|title=Bundesliga Historie 2004/05|language=German|publisher=kicker}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{Fussballdaten|marcelinho|Marcelinho}}\n*