 Tseckares Inc.]].<ref>{{cite news|last1=Lisa|first1=Prevost|title=Hartford\u2019s Booster in Chief|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2007/06/24/realestate/24wczo.html?_r=0|accessdate=2 August 2015|agency=The New York Times|publisher=The New York Times Company|date=27 June 2007}}</ref> Construction began in June 2004 and was completed in 2006 by [[Turner Construction]]. It cost nearly $200 million to complete with $32.5 million coming in a grant from the state.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Seay |first1=Gregory |title=Hartford 21: The tower Northland got right |url=http://www.hartfordbusiness.com/article/20180709/PRINTEDITION/307059959/hartford-21-the-tower-northland-got-right |website=hartfordbusiness.com |publisher=Hartford Business Journal |accessdate=29 November 2018}}</ref>  \n\nThere are 36 floors aboveground and three below. The building contains 262 luxury apartments as well as lower level retail and office space. It is the tallest building constructed in Hartford in the 21st century. \n\n==History== \n[[File:HartfordSkyline-Int84Ramps (36127789953).jpg|thumb|Hartford 21 is second from left]]\nHartford 21 was completed in 2006, and is purported to be the tallest residential tower between [[New York City]] and [[Boston]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Hartford 21|url=http://www.emporis.com/buildings/101592/hartford-21-hartford-ct-usa|website=Emporis|publisher=Emporis|accessdate=2 August 2015}}</ref> It is located adjacent to the [[XL Center]], near where Asylum Street intersects Trumbull Street.\n\n\n==See also==\n*[[List of tallest buildings in Hartford]]\n*[[List of tallest buildings by U.S. state]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n[[Category:Skyscrapers in Hartford, Connecticut]]\n[[Category:Residential skyscrapers in Connecticut]]\n\n\n{{Connecticut-struct-stub}}\n", "name_user": "John of Reading", "label": "safe", "comment": "Generalfixes, corrected a website name", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hartford_21"}
